name: McMillan Hall, Washington University in St. Louis
directions: There are two accessible unisex toilets in the northern hallway of this building. One on the first floor and one on the second floor. Take a right out of the elevator and go through the first section, then through the foyer and then halfway down the second section.
comment:
It's on a college campus so most assume you're a student or faculty member. Building locks after 6pm unless you have a Wash U ID badge.
Building is basically a box, but the many doors and stairwells make it confusing af. Elevator is located at the northwest corner.

Latitude And Longitude (45.734231,-109.757844) 
Rest area is open 24/7/365. 4 "mens" restrooms on the left, 4 "womens" restrooms on the right. Changing table in first restroom on both sides. 
8 TOTAL single user gendered restrooms with solid locking doors. 
These are some of the best and in excellent condition for several states in any direction including CA & WA

Latitude And Longitude (45.735871,-109.756590)
